# Async & I/O Rules

- Use `async def` / `await` for ALL network I/O (HTTP requests, API calls).
- Use `httpx.AsyncClient` (not `requests`) for all outbound HTTP.
- Implement exponential backoff via `tenacity` for retryable errors (429, 503).
- Rate-limit all external calls via `utils/rate_limiter.py` — never call APIs in tight loops.
- Always set a `timeout=` on every network call. Default: 30 seconds.
- Handle `asyncio.CancelledError` explicitly in long-running tasks.
- Use `asyncio.gather()` with `return_exceptions=True` when running modules in parallel.

# Proxy & Stealth (utils/proxy.py)
- All outbound scraping requests MUST route through the proxy manager.
- Rotate User-Agent headers on every request using a predefined pool.
- Honour `robots.txt` — check before scraping any domain.
- The proxy manager must support a `dry_run=True` mode that logs requests without sending.